Perth Railway StationServing the City of Perth as our primary access to the rail lines, the current Perth Railway Station has stood in place on Wellington Street for over 100 years, having replaced the original station which had first opened to the public in 1881.
— The Daily News, 4 June 1891
— The Inquirer and Commercial News, 7 October 1898
